I"ƒ<p>The agent is distributed as a Docker image. The image bundles the agentâ€™s source code, a Python 3 environment, and the AWS command line tools.</p>

<p>Execute the agent with a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">docker run</code> command that references the image on Docker Hub. Youâ€™ll use bind mounts and environment variables to configure it with your YAML file and credentials.</p>

<ul>
  <li>The YAML configuration file youâ€™ve created should be provided to the container via a bind mount. The syntax for providing a bind mount is:
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      --mount type=bind,source=&lt;host_path&gt;,target=&lt;container_path&gt;
  </code></p>
    <p>The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">host_path</code> should be the full path to where youâ€™ve stored the YAML configuration file. The <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">container_path</code> must be <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">/home/jf_agent/config.yml</code>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Your credentials should be provided to the container via environment variables. The syntax for providing environment variables from a file is:
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      --env-file &lt;full_path_to_env_file&gt;
  </code></p>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 id="sample-run-commands">Sample run commands</h2>

<p>Below are some common use cases for running the agent, and their corresponding <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">docker run</code> commands.</p>

<p><strong>Please be sure to update the commands with the proper paths when copying them!</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Normal mode: download and send
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      docker pull jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable &amp;&amp; \<br />
      docker run --rm \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/ourconfig.yml,target=/home/jf_agent/config.yml \<br />
      --env-file /full/path/creds.env \<br />
      jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable<br />
  </code></p>
  </li>
  <li>Download data without sending
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      docker pull jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable &amp;&amp; docker run --rm \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/ourconfig.yml,target=/home/jf_agent/config.yml \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/jf_agent_output,target=/home/jf_agent/output \<br />
      --env-file ./creds.env \<br />
      jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable -m download_only<br />
  </code></p>
  </li>
  <li>Send previously downloaded data
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      docker pull jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable &amp;&amp; docker run --rm \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/ourconfig.yml,target=/home/jf_agent/config.yml \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/jf_agent_output,target=/home/jf_agent/output \<br />
      --env-file ./creds.env \<br />
      jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable -m send_only -od ./output/20190822_133513<br />
  </code></p>
  </li>
  <li>Print info on Jira fields
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      docker pull jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable &amp;&amp; docker run --rm \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/ourconfig.yml,target=/home/jf_agent/config.yml \<br />
      --env-file ./creds.env \<br />
      jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable -m print_all_jira_fields<br />
  </code></p>
  </li>
  <li>Print Git repos apparently missing from Jellyfish
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      docker pull jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable &amp;&amp; docker run --rm \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/ourconfig.yml,target=/home/jf_agent/config.yml \<br />
      --env-file ./creds.env \<br />
      jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable -m print_apparently_missing_git_repos<br />
  </code></p>
  </li>
  <li>Validate configuration
    <p class="code-block"><code>
      docker pull jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable &amp;&amp; docker run --rm \<br />
      --mount type=bind,source=/full/path/ourconfig.yml,target=/home/jf_agent/config.yml \<br />
      --env-file ./creds.env \<br />
      jellyfishco/jf_agent:stable -m validate<br />
  </code></p>
  </li>
</ul>

